      	<div class="row">
          <div class="large-6 columns">
            <h4>About Me</h4> 
            <p>
              I'm a graduate student in WVU's Department of
              Statistics working on my M.Sc. in Statistics.  I earned
              my B.Sc. in Computer Science at California University of
              Pennsylvania with a minor in Mathemetics.  My focus is on
              on Computational Statistics, Data Technologies,
              and Statistical Programming.  
            </p>
            <p>
              I got my start in statistics while doing my undergrad in CS  writing software to analyze literature with the 
              <a href="http://wheatoncollege.edu/lexomics/" target="_blank">Wheaton Lexomics Group</a>. Writing programs
              to implement unsupervised machine learning algorithms sparked my interest in all things data, and I haven't
              looked back since.
            </p>
          </div>
	  <vr>
            <div class="large-6 columns">
              <h5>Recent Experience</h5>
              <p>
		As a grad student, I'm grateful to have had the chance to work with some extraordinary researchers, like
		developing sociolinguistic models with Kirk Hazen and the 
		<a href="http://dialects.english.wvu.edu/" target="_blank">West Virginia Dialect Project</a>  
		and helping Dr. James Harner develop state of the art Data Science courses.
              </p>
	      <h5>Goals</h5>
              <p>
		After finishing my Master's, I'm hoping to find a challenging position
		in industry where I can leverage my experience in 
		software development, statistical analysis, data technologies, data visualization,
		and machine learning to make data-driven policy recommendations.
	      </p>
            </div>
	</div>
